733271f-a.title: Squatters Colony near 19th Street and 10th Avenue.
733271f-a.text:
Shack of a unemployed squatter, near 19th Street west of Tenth Ave. This clearance is in preparation for a railroad right-of-way, as part of municipal plans for improving west side of the city. (Manhattan).
July 16, 1932.

P.L. Sperr.
